09/08/2009
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- A Podgorica court convicted on Friday (August 7th) six members of a criminal group who killed a senior police officer in the summer of 2005.
Each of the convicts was sentenced to 30 years in prison.
According to the conviction, police officer Slavoljub Scekic was killed because of his involvement in the investigation of several bomb attacks at a luxury hotel on the Adriatic Coast.
(AP, Vecernje Novosti, RTS, Kurir, B92 - 07/08/09)
